        <h2>Syllabus</h2>
        <p class="muted">Overview</p>
        <p>This course introduces principles of information and communication systems with emphasis on networks, protocols, and real-world applications. Learning outcomes include designing communication solutions, analysing protocols, and implementing small-scale networked systems.</p>

        <h3 style="margin-top:12px">Assessment</h3>
        <ul style="padding-left:18px;color:var(--muted)">
          <li>Assignments: 35%</li>
          <li>Midterm exam: 25%</li>
          <li>Final exam / project: 30%</li>
          <li>Participation & quizzes: 10%</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="margin-top:12px">Course policy</h3>
        <ul style="padding-left:18px;color:var(--muted)">
          <li>Late submissions: up to 3 days with 10% penalty per day unless excused.</li>
          <li>Academic integrity: Plagiarism is not tolerated. Cite sources.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

